The family of one of the five men arrested as part of massive anti-terrorism raids in Melbourne were warned by police were falling victim to Islamic State recruiters .
Ahead of the arrests that stopped an alleged terrorist attack planned for Anzac Day , ASIO contacted the families of some of the would-be killers and cautioned them the men were becoming radicalised .
The family were told to stop their son communicating with the extremist recruiter , who groomed Melbourne terrorist Numan Haider .
Police say the threat was ` fully contained .